&lt;p data-start=&quot;379&quot; data-end=&quot;615&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;439&quot; data-end=&quot;452&quot;&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Bremen, Germany — On-site&lt;br data-start=&quot;478&quot; data-end=&quot;481&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;481&quot; data-end=&quot;496&quot;&gt;Reports to:&lt;/strong&gt; the Head of PR &amp;amp; Events&lt;br data-start=&quot;520&quot; data-end=&quot;523&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;523&quot; data-end=&quot;543&quot;&gt;Employment type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time&lt;br data-start=&quot;553&quot; data-end=&quot;556&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;556&quot; data-end=&quot;567&quot;&gt;Travel:&lt;/strong&gt; Up to 30% Germany, Switzerland, international&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;617&quot; data-end=&quot;907&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for an &lt;strong&gt;Event Manager based in Bremen or Hanover &lt;/strong&gt;to lead a calendar that spans scientific conferences, partner and business summits, town halls, programme launches, press events, student life and campus celebrations, graduations, and executive convenings across the &lt;strong&gt;Constructor ecosystem&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;909&quot; data-end=&quot;912&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;1l4u08w&quot; data-start=&quot;957&quot; data-end=&quot;977&quot;&gt;About Constructor&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;979&quot; data-end=&quot;1260&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/&quot;&gt;Constructor&lt;/a&gt; is an international ecosystem spanning education, research, and technology. It includes &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.university/&quot;&gt;Constructor University Bremen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Constructor Tech&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/knowledge&quot;&gt;Constructor Knowledge&lt;/a&gt;, and partner entities such as EBAC, working together to advance how knowledge is created, taught, and applied.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1262&quot; data-end=&quot;1417&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/knowledge&quot;&gt;Constructor Knowledge&lt;/a&gt; sits at the heart of this ecosystem — connecting students, faculty, partners, media, and industry across our entities and programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;1wdgaw5&quot; data-start=&quot;1419&quot; data-end=&quot;1436&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1438&quot; data-end=&quot;1720&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for an &lt;strong&gt;Event Manager based in Bremen or Hanover&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to take ownership of a calendar that spans scientific conferences, partner and business summits, town halls, product and programme launches, press events, student life and campus celebrations, graduations, and executive convenings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1722&quot; data-end=&quot;2066&quot;&gt;You&#39;ll be the operational and creative lead for online, offline, and hybrid events serving students, faculty, staff, prospects, partners, media, and the broader Constructor community. The role reports to the Head of PR &amp;amp; Events and works closely with marketing, academic leadership, and executive teams across multiple countries and time zones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;2068&quot; data-end=&quot;2351&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a hands-on role in a fast-moving environment. &lt;/strong&gt;You should be equally comfortable shaping the concept for a flagship conference, negotiating with a Bremen catering vendor, briefing a &lt;strong&gt;Nobel laureate guest speaker&lt;/strong&gt;, and troubleshooting AV ten minutes before a town hall goes live.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;164ko59&quot; data-start=&quot;2353&quot; data-end=&quot;2371&quot;&gt;What you&#39;ll own&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;2373&quot; data-end=&quot;2691&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;2373&quot; data-end=&quot;2405&quot;&gt;Event strategy and planning.&lt;/strong&gt; Translate the annual event plan into concrete proposals — formats, agendas, ven

&lt;div class=&quot;job-preview job-details__preview container&quot; data-test-component=&quot;job-preview&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-preview__job-details&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-preview__description &quot; data-test-description=&quot;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job title: Executive &amp;amp; Personal Assistant (Team-Based Role)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Remote with frequent travel!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Constructor Group&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2019 by tech and education entrepreneur Dr. Serg Bell, Constructor Group is a global institution dedicated to revolutionizing education and driving innovation in Machine Intelligence, Quantum Technology, Intelligent Materials, Hybrid Reality, and Life Engineering. Our ecosystem includes Constructor Knowledge, offering education tools and services worldwide; Constructor, a software company delivering advanced tech solutions; and Constructor Capital, providing early-stage funding for science, technology, and digital transformation projects. Backed by a diverse network of academic partners, business leaders, and Nobel laureates, Constructor Group is redefining education and technology for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an Executive &amp;amp; Personal Assistant to support the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.oznurbell.com/&quot;&gt;Chairwoman of Constructor University Bremen and CEO of Constructor Knowledge&lt;/a&gt; as part of a dedicated support team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-trust, high-responsibility role combining executive-level business support with personal and lifestyle coordination in an international environment. The role is not a standalone assistant position; you will work closely with other assistants and team members to ensure seamless coverage across professional and private matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key focus areas include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complex calendar, time, and priority management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;International travel and logistics (business &amp;amp; personal)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive meetings, board support, and follow-ups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-quality document and presentation preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal logistics coordination (appointments, family travel, lifestyle support)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Absolute confidentiality and trusted gatekeeping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires comfort managing both business and highly personal matters with professionalism, discretion, and sound judgment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideal profile:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting senior executives, founders, or principals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calm, proactive, and detail-oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent English; additional languages a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working as part of a support team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;📍 International scope | ✈️ Travel required | 🔒 High confidentiality&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE CONSTRUCTOR GROUP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/&quot;&gt;Constructor Group&lt;/a&gt; is driven by the belief that knowledge is the solution to all evil. We are a global institution focused on making scientists, teachers, and students more effective and efficient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our integrated ecosystem focuses on fundamental technology needs relevant to science and education: generative AI, MetaPresence, computing, robotics, energy, health &amp;amp; bio, and neuroscience. &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/&quot;&gt;Constructor Group&lt;/a&gt; consists of three main pillars – &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/knowledge&quot;&gt;Constructor Knowledge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Constructor Capital&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.tech/?__hstc=100175169.8b0f85aa87aedb5f1cdd10e6c30d8a9b.1778592930857.1778592930857.1778592930857.1&amp;amp;__hssc=100175169.5.1778592430017&amp;amp;__hsfp=97c674a0edf8603ac2ef39b43750c9e0&quot;&gt;Constructor Tech&lt;/a&gt; – uniting science, technology, and education around a single deeply fundamental and yet very applied mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Constructor Group is looking for a Head of Engineering to lead the company’s technology and software development function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for defining and executing the technology strategy, managing engineering teams, ensuring high-quality product delivery, and building scalable, reliable, and secure technology solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a strong technical leader with a hands-on engineering background, experience managing development teams, and the ability to align technology decisions with business goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the software development function and manage engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute the technology strategy in alignment with business and product goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the development roadmap together with product, business, and executive stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely and high-quality delivery of software products and technical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable, secure, and reliable architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and improve engineering processes, development standards, code quality, and release management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage technical priorities, resource allocation, and delivery risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, mentor, and develop engineering managers, team leads, architects, and developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support recruitment, onboarding, and performance management for technical teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive best practices in software development, testing, DevOps, security, and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and select technologies, tools, frameworks, and vendors when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate technical decisions, risks, and progress to senior leadership in a clear, business-oriented way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience as a CTO, Head of Engineering, VP Engineering, Head of Development, or similar senior technology leadership role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong hands-on background in software engineering and system architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing engineering teams and technical managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of modern software development practices, cloud infrastructure, DevOps, CI/CD, security, and scalable architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience delivering complex digital products or platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to balance strategic technology vision with hands-on execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership, problem-solving, and decision-making skills.

&lt;p&gt;As &lt;strong&gt;Lead Executive Assistant &amp;amp; Private Office Operations Manager (CEO Office)&lt;/strong&gt; of Constructor Group, you will operate at the centre of a dynamic, global ecosystem spanning Germany, Turkey, and Bulgaria. This position is designed for an experienced professional with&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;15+ years of proven excellence in executive operations&lt;/strong&gt;, project leadership, or private office management — someone who combines operational precision, strategic judgment, and the stamina to lead in a constantly changing, high-performance environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior, hands-on leadership role combining Executive Assistant &amp;amp; Personal Assistant, Private Office, and team management responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will manage and develop a team of &lt;strong&gt;Executive Assistants and 10–15 supporting personas (drivers, chefs, housekeepers, coordinators, etc.)&lt;/strong&gt;, ensuring flawless coordination across all aspects of the CEO’s professional and personal ecosystem. Your ultimate mission is simple but demanding: to maximise the CEO’s productivity, anticipate needs before they arise, and make the impossible happen smoothly and discreetly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a highly hands-on leadership role. &lt;/strong&gt;While you will manage and develop the administrative support team, you will also personally execute critical Executive Assistant and Personal Assistant tasks for the CEO when needed. The successful candidate must be comfortable switching between strategic coordination, team leadership, and direct, hands-on support — including calendar management, travel coordination, personal errands, vendor communication, last-minute problem solving, and confidential personal matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More about the CEO &lt;a href=&quot;https://arici.com/&quot;&gt;Serg Bell&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;2814&quot; data-end=&quot;2855&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;2814&quot; data-end=&quot;2855&quot;&gt;Hands-on Executive &amp;amp; Personal Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;2857&quot; data-end=&quot;3368&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;sgmqc3&quot; data-start=&quot;2857&quot; data-end=&quot;2972&quot;&gt;Personally support the CEO with high-priority executive and personal tasks when direct involvement is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;18vs1dh&quot; data-start=&quot;2973&quot; data-end=&quot;3143&quot;&gt;Manage last-minute calendar changes, urgent travel needs, personal logistics, family coordination, household/service provider communication, and confidential errands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1r78g2v&quot; data-start=&quot;3144&quot; data-end=&quot;3271&quot;&gt;Step in directly when the team is unavailable, overloaded, or when the task requires senior judgment, discretion, or speed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1e684ig&quot; data-start=&quot;3272&quot; data-end=&quot;3368&quot;&gt;Balance leadership responsibilities with direct execution; this role is not purely managerial.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Team Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and structure a high-performing administrative team (3–4 Executive Assistants and 10–15 support personnel).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create clarity of roles, responsibilities, and workflows to ensure seamless execution of all tasks across time zones and geographies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and enforce SOPs, checklists, and productivity tools that bring structure to complex, parallel workstreams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary interface between the CEO, Chief of Staff, and broader support network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&qu

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Constructor Group:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2019 by tech entrepreneur Dr. Serg Bell, Constructor Group is a global institution advancing education and innovation in AI, Quantum Technology, Intelligent Materials, Hybrid Reality, and Life Engineering. Its ecosystem includes Constructor Knowledge (education solutions), Constructor Tech (technology products), and Constructor Capital (early-stage investments), working together to shape the future of education and technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Collection &amp;amp; Analysis: Gather, clean, and analyse quantitative and qualitative data from various sources (surveys, industry reports, enrolment data, etc.) to understand market trends, demographics, and learner preferences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Insights Generation: Prepare and present reports that provide actionable insights on key market trends, competitors, and customer segments for both higher education and adult education markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Research Initiatives: Assist in designing research methodologies, developing survey questionnaires, and managing data collection for market research projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitor Analysis: Conduct ongoing competitor analysis to monitor trends in program offerings, pricing, and market positioning within the education industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration: Work closely with cross-functional teams to align research insights with strategic goals, contributing to the development of new programs, marketing initiatives, and student engagement strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General Assistance: Complete other tasks as assigned by the Senior Market Research Analyst to support the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 1-3 years of experience in market research or related fields such as banking, consulting, or e-commerce, with a strong foundation in data analysis and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: Relevant Bachelor’s degree; a Master’s degree is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Skills: Proficiency in data analysis tools (e.g., Excel, SPSS, Tableau) and survey platforms. Comfortable working with large datasets and digital research tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technology &amp;amp; AI Curiosity: Interest in emerging technologies and AI-powered tools (e.g., ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, AI coding assistants, and workflow automation tools), with the curiosity and willingness to explore new ways of improving research workflows through automation, dashboards, databases, and other digital solutions. Basic coding knowledge (e.g., SQL, Python, or similar) is a plus but not required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remote Work Discipline: Ability to stay organized, manage workload proactively, and maintain productivity while working independently in a remote setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical Mindset: Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret complex data, identify trends, and translate findings into actionable recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication Skills: Excellent written and verbal communication skills to create clear, concise reports and presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to Detail: High level of accuracy and attention to detail, ensuring data integrity and reliable insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in Education: Passionate about contributing to the higher education and adult education sectors, with a willingness to learn and adapt to the specific needs of these fields.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Language Proficiency: Advanced proficiency in English is essential, with strong communication skills in both written and spoken forms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;job-preview job-details__preview container&quot; data-test-component=&quot;job-preview&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-preview__job-details&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-preview__description &quot; data-test-description=&quot;&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a reliable, discreet, and highly organised &lt;strong&gt;Personal Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; to provide part-time support in Geneva.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is primarily focused on personal assistance, day-to-day coordination, administrative support, scheduling, and communication. The ideal candidate is proactive, detail-oriented, comfortable handling confidential matters, and able to work independently with minimal supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in &lt;strong&gt;academic organisations, universities, research institutions, or education-related environments&lt;/strong&gt; would be considered a strong advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide day-to-day personal and administrative support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage calendars, appointments, meetings, and personal schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate travel arrangements, reservations, logistics, and related documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with personal errands, coordination with service providers, and household or lifestyle-related tasks where needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare, organise, and maintain documents, records, and correspondence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle confidential information with a high level of discretion and professionalism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with internal and external stakeholders&lt;strong&gt; in English and French. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with event, meeting, or visit coordination when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support expense tracking, invoices, payments, and basic administrative follow-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure smooth coordination between different parties and timely completion of tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications and Experience:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience as a &lt;strong&gt;Personal Assistant&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Executive Assistant&lt;/strong&gt;, or in a similar support role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fluent in English and French, both written and spoken.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based in Geneva or able to work regularly from Geneva. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organisational and time-management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of discretion, confidentiality, and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities and work independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible, hands-on, and service-oriented approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good knowledge of Microsoft Office and general digital tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in an &lt;strong&gt;academic organisation&lt;/strong&gt;, university, research institution, educational foundation, or similar environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with international environments and multicultural communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting senior-level individuals or private clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE СONSTRUCTOR GROUP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/&quot;&gt;Constructor Group&lt;/a&gt; is driven by the belief that knowledge is the solution to all evil. We are a global institution focused on making scientists, teachers, and students more effective and efficient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our integrated ecosystem focuses on fundamental technology needs relevant to science and education: generative AI, MetaPresence, computing, robotics, energy, health &amp;amp; bio, and neuroscience. &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/&quot;&gt;Constructor Group&lt;/a&gt; consists of three main pillars – &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/knowledge&quot;&gt;Constructor Knowledge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Constructor Capital&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.tech/?__hstc=100175169.8b0f85aa87aedb5f1cdd10e6c30d8a9b.1778592930857.1778592930857.1778592930857.1&amp;amp;__hssc=100175169.5.1778592430017&amp;amp;__hsfp=97c674a0edf8603ac2ef39b43750c9e0&quot;&gt;Constructor Tech&lt;/a&gt; – uniting science, technology, and education around a single deeply fundamental and yet very applied mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Constructor Group is looking for a President / Head of Corporate Development, Argentina &amp;amp; LATAM to lead the development and expansion of the Group’s presence across Argentina and the wider Latin American region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior strategic and operational role focused on building local market presence, developing partnerships, supporting business growth, and ensuring smooth coordination between regional teams and the global organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines strong business development experience, operational leadership, stakeholder management, and a deep understanding of the LATAM market. This role is similar in scope to a senior cross-functional leadership position, but with a clear regional focus on Argentina and Latin America.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead corporate development initiatives across Argentina and LATAM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with local partners, universities, institutions, government bodies, investors, and business communities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify new business opportunities, strategic partnerships, and market expansion opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the company in the region and act as the key senior point of contact for local stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development and execution of the regional growth strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with global leadership across business, finance, legal, HR, operations, and product teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help establish and scale local operations, processes, and teams where needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor market trends, the competitive landscape, the regulatory environment, and regional business opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support negotiations, partnership agreements, and strategic initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment between local execution and global company priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare regular updates, reports, and recommendations for senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in corporate development, business development, general management, strategy, or regional leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of the Argentina and/or LATAM business environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with international companies or global stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong network across business, education, technology, government, or investment ecosystems would be a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build trusted relationships with senior stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
