&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core procurement&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full procurement cycle from requisition to purchase order to delivery and payment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source, evaluate, and onboard suppliers across all indirect categories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate commercial terms, pricing, SLAs, and renewals, and lead contract negotiations to close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own vendor relationship management, including performance reviews, escalations, and risk monitoring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run competitive tenders and RFPs, build comparison models, and make sourcing recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and control spend against budget, identify savings, and report on procurement KPIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the contract repository, renewal calendar, and supplier master data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with internal policy, data protection requirements, and licensing terms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve procurement processes, tooling, and approval workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project leadership:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead one-time and cross-functional procurement projects end to end&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate vendors, contractors, and internal teams to deliver on time and on budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage project risks, dependencies, and stakeholder communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure results against the business case and report outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of procurement or purchasing experience across multiple indirect categories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in international procurement, sourcing and managing suppliers across multiple countries and regions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Higher education in economics, business, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid working knowledge of the IT category, covering all types of hardware, software licensing models, SaaS subscriptions, cloud services, and colocation and server housing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading or coordinating cross-functional projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial and contract literacy, comfortable shaping terms alongside Legal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical skills for spend analysis, cost modelling, total cost of ownership, and ROI assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident stakeholder management across technical and non-technical teams and all seniority levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with ERP systems and strong spreadsheet skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent English, written and verbal (additional languages are an advantage)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented, organised, and able to run many parallel suppliers and projects at once&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

