&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly organised and analytical &lt;strong&gt;Property Project Manager (PPM)&lt;/strong&gt; to oversee the acquisition, renovation, and property management of the Company&#39;s corporate (commercial) and private real estate in Bremen, Germany, and across multiple international locations (Singapore, Italy, Switzerland, etc.). PPM reports to the Senior Manager, Development &amp;amp; Construction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is comfortable generating and managing complex projects, monitoring interim results vs contractual obligations, reviewing project status reports from contractors, controlling budget fulfilment, making on-site visits (various jurisdictions), and securing high-quality standards. On-site visits may be done depending on the project’s complexity, stage and existing resources in the respective locations. Fluency in German and English is required; proficiency in Russian and other languages is beneficial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Planning &amp;amp; Coordination&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the real estate management team by constantly monitoring the projects’ status and developing possibilities for the next steps in the projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage development and renovation projects from acquisition and early planning through completion in close coordination with the Line manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Search for contractors, negotiate project terms and timelines, track milestones and deliverables across multiple properties and countries remotely or in person (if needed)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On behalf of the Company’s team, act as the central point of contact between the company, authorities, contractors, consultants, and service providers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the acquisition team in gaining actual information and photo documentation from sites, including with the help of contractors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement contractual terms for the 3d party service providers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Budgeting &amp;amp; Approval Processes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare preliminary budgets and cost estimates based on market research and preliminary tendering of the works&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal budget approval processes and monitor expenditures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track variations, invoices, and overall cost alignment with approved budgets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Property Assessment &amp;amp; Documentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and manage condition assessments of different properties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compile structured photo and video documentation reports before, during, and after projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear digital records of property conditions, progress updates, and decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contractor &amp;amp; Vendor Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research, identify, and pre-select properties, contractors, architects, designers, and suppliers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Request, compare, and analyse offers and proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate tendering processes and support contractor selection in line with the existing procurement policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor contractor performance, timelines, and compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Give feedback on the potential contractors with preferences, strong and weak sides in their work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
