&lt;p&gt;As the &lt;strong&gt;Senior Executive Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; to the Founder of Constructor Group, you will play a critical role in supporting a dynamic and fast-paced executive office. This is a high-exposure position requiring exceptional organisational, project, and time-management skills. You will be responsible for handling a wide range of administrative, logistical, and scheduling tasks for &lt;strong&gt;the CEO and, on occasion, his family.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for individuals who thrive in demanding environments, are proactive problem-solvers, and are committed to delivering excellence in executive support. The ideal candidate is highly organized, discreet, detail-oriented, and capable of independently managing multiple priorities with flexibility and composure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More about the CEO &lt;a href=&quot;https://arici.com/&quot;&gt;Serg Bell&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide high-level administrative support, including &lt;strong&gt;managing complex calendars, scheduling meetings, organizing travel, and preparing briefings and materials&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
