&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a&amp;nbsp;senior, hands-on role responsible for the complete technology environment of a CEO, executive team, and their families across 5+ private residences and 6+ offices in EMEA and Singapore. The role requires full ownership of IT infrastructure, devices, connectivity, and physical security technology ensuring guaranteed continuity under any operational conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain seamless, continuously validated technology environments across all locations: laptops, tablets, mobile devices, monitors, AV equipment, and Zoom Rooms. Deliver expert support for Microsoft 365, Teams, Zoom, Windows, macOS, and mobile devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, deploy, and manage multi-site network infrastructure including LAN/WAN, managed switches, Wi-Fi, firewalls, and network segmentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and support satellite connectivity (Starlink) for maritime and remote locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage physical security technology: CCTV, IP cameras, NVR systems, and access control across all managed properties.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide on-demand support to executive family members on personal devices and home office setups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle physical setup and installation of technology equipment at residences and ensure fully operational, secure technology setups during business travel — including hotels, vehicles, and yachts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage all IT assets across locations: device inventories, software licenses, and subscriptions, with proactive refresh cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and maintain cybersecurity controls appropriate to high-value individuals: endpoint protection, MDM, firewall configuration, anti-malware, and secure VPN.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct proactive testing of all equipment and conferencing systems ahead of meetings and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain current documentation of system configurations, operational procedures, and issue resolutions across all locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be available on-call for urgent support outside business hours under a structured on-call arrangement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience providing direct IT support to C-suite or VIP principals with personal accountability for their technology environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on network engineering competency: routing, switching, Wi-Fi, firewall management, VPN, and multi-site WAN.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Windows, macOS, iOS, Microsoft 365, and Zoom. Ability to quickly learn new technologies and software stacks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical experience with Starlink or equivalent satellite connectivity platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with physical security systems: IP CCTV, NVR/DVR, and access control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of endpoint security, backup, and recovery in high-value individual contexts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to own technical problems end-to-end without reliance on external vendors for routine issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English required; German, Russian, or Turkish is an advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated discretion and professionalism in confidential personal and executive environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
